(8, 6, 7, 'MCA', 'top', 0, 'what-is-mca-master-of-computer-application', 'What is MCA (Master of Computer Application)', '<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">MCA (Master of Computer Application) is a post graduation course of 3 years. Students with bachelor degree of minimum 3 years with Mathematics in 10+2 level or graduation level from a recognized University are eligible for this degree.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">This course focuses towards application development in field of Information Technology. It also focuses on latest technology and programming languages to provide a base background of IT for students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">This course covers algorithm design, database management, computational theory, network management, electronics, mathematics, mobile technologies, programming, statistics, account, finance etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;"><span data-mce-style="line-height: 1.5;" style="line-height: 1.5;">With the growing use of computers and internet, the popularity of computer education has also increased over the past few years. Students are selecting the computer field as their future scope of work. Demand for computer experts is increasing in not only India but also in other countries. In near future, there will be more growth in the demand of computer specialized people. So it is a good choice to make a career in computer field.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">By choosing MCA course, students will be able to get a job opportunities from big IT companies like Wipro, IBM, Oracle, TCS etc. All these companies offer great job opportunities to IT students with MCA degree. After completing MCA degree, a student can work as a system analyst, system developer, software developer, system manager, web designer, IT consultant, IT education etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">There are also some good career options in Government sector for MCA degree holders. There are many job opportunities for MCA degree holders in government field. You can go through the government website for employment news regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">One of the best benefit of pursing MCA is, working as a freelancer. After you computer your MCA course, you may choose your career as a freelancer. There are many things you can do as a freelancer. There are some websites and companies who provide work for freelancers in India. You can work from your home.</p>', '', 'What is Master of Computer Application (MCA)', 'Master of Computer Application is a post graduation degree of 3 years. By choosing MCA as your career, you can open paths to different IT industries for jobs.', 'master of computer application,it course,post graduation course', '2013-09-26', 1),
(9, 0, 7, '', '', 0, 'privacy-policy', 'Privacy Policy', '<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">Careerask.com takes this privacy policy seriously and strictly adheres to it. Any personal information you provide us including your name, website URL, address and email address will not be released, sold or rented to anyone outside Careerask.com</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">Usage of Information Collected</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">We collect and use the data c ontained in log files. The information in the log files include your IP address, your ISP, browser you used to visit our site, time you have visited our site and pages you visited throughout our site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">This site uses Google Analytics automatically receive and record information from your brower, including your IP address, cookie information, and the page you request. As said, such information will not be released, rented or sold outside of Careerask.com</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">Usage of Cookies and Web beacons<br />\r\nA &quot;cookie&quot; is a small text file placed in your computer and allows Careerask.com to recognize you the next time you visit. Cookies does not contain any of your personal information, and Careerask.com does not use cookies to collect information. These cookies might be collected by 3rd party content providers such as online advertising companies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">We use third-party advertising companies to serve ads when you visit our website. These companies may use information (not including your name, address, email address, or telephone number) about your visits to this and other websites in order to provide advertisemetns about goods and services of interest to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">Google&#39;s use of the DART cookie enables it to serve ads to you based on your visit to our sites and other sites on the Internet. You may opt out of the use of DART cookie by visiting the Google ad and content network privacy policy. However, this can affect how you are able to interact with our site as well as other websites. This could include the inability to login to services or programs, such as logging into forums ora ccounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">Privacy Policy Changes<br />\r\nWe may update the policy in future. In case of such an event, the changes will be reflected in this page. If you have any doubts, you can email us at admin@careerask.com</p>', '', 'Privacy Policy', 'Privacy Policy  of Career Ask', 'privacy policy', '2013-09-26', 1),
(10, 6, 7, 'MBA', '', 0, 'what-is-mba-master-of-business-administration', 'What is MBA (Master of Business Administration)', '<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">MBA (Master of Business Administration) is a post graduation degree of 2 years. Anyone with a 3 years bachelor degree can apply for MBA course. Students with MBA degree can make career in management and leadership roles in organizations. This course mainly focuses on developing the skills for sales, marketing, brand management and supply chain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">MBA degree holders get hired so companies can utilize the full potential of their business skills for their companies growth. A person with MBA degree is usually considered helpful to achieve optimal profitability and growth of business. MBA course provides you a skill-set for developing finance, strategic planning, economics, systems, marketing, resources management, and basic accounting. An individual can make a good career by achieving all these skills through this MBA course.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">Saying that, MBA graduates are required in almost every industry, wouldn&rsquo;t be wrong. It is a true thing and totally acceptable. You can get a good opportunity in sales, marketing, supply chain, international business and human resource management departments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">It is on a person whether he/she would like to go into a services and product sector, industrial sector, financial sector, Telecom sector, NGO sector, marketing sector or education management sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">There are different varieties of specialization can be acquired in MBA degree which includes Finance, services, health, human resources, information technology, media, telecommunications etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">To get admission in MBA, there are some entrance exams held which is CAT, MAT etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">MBA degree is becoming a trend in youth nowadays because it gives you the result as soon as you complete your education and get a job. After receiving your MBA degree you can choose one of below fields as your career-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); orphans: 4; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px;">1. Management Consulting<br />\r\n2. Analyst<br />\r\n3. Entrepreneurship<br />\r\n4. Investment banking<br />\r\n5. Sales<br />\r\n6. Private Equity / Venture Capital<br />\r\n7. HR Manager<br />\r\n8. Quality Manager<br />\r\n9. ERP Consultant<br />\r\n10 Project Manager</p>', '', 'What is MBA (Master of Business Administration)', 'Master of Business Administration (MBA) is a course suitable for someone who believes to make a career in marketing, finance and management.', 'master of business administration,mba course,mba degree,business course,post graduation course,post graduation degree', '2013-09-26', 1),
